            <div class="product">
                <h3>Overview of the Super System</h3>
                <p>The Super System is a conservative and flexible trading strategy designed to work across different timeframes, suitable for scalpers, swing traders, and long-term traders. It focuses on providing secure signals by utilizing a set of technical indicators to confirm trade entries. The system aims to minimize false signals and maximize profits through disciplined trading rules.</p>

                <h3>System Components & Indicators</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Timeframe:</strong> Any timeframe can be used.</li>
                    <li><strong>Currency Pairs:</strong> Major pairs like EUR/USD and GBP/USD.</li>
                    <li><strong>Indicators:</strong>
                        <ul>
                            <li>3 EMA (Exponential Moving Average) set to close price.</li>
                            <li>5 EMA (Exponential Moving Average) set to open price.</li>
                            <li>34 EMA (Exponential Moving Average) set to close price.</li>
                            <li>89 EMA (Exponential Moving Average) set to close price.</li>
                            <li>3 RSI (Relative Strength Index) with levels at 20 and 80.</li>
                            <li>Stochastic (5,3,3) with default settings and levels at 20 and 80.</li>
                            <li>14 ADX (Average Directional Movement Index) with +D and –D line only.</li>
                        </ul>
                    </li>
                </ul>

                <h3>Buy Rules</h3>
                <p>To enter a long (buy) trade, the following conditions must be met:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li>The 34 EMA must be above the 89 EMA.</li>
                    <li>The 3 RSI must cross above the 80 level.</li>
                    <li>The Stochastic must be above its Signal line.</li>
                    <li>The +D ADX line must be above the –D line.</li>
                    <li>The 3 EMA must cross above the 5 EMA.</li>
                    <li>When all these rules are satisfied, a buy trade can be opened.</li>
                    <li>Set the Stop Loss below the 34 EMA or the last swing low point.</li>
                    <li>Set the Take Profit at double the amount of the Stop Loss, or close the trade when an opposite signal is given by the 3 and 5 EMAs, 3 RSI, or ADX indicators (opposite signal: 3 EMA below 5 EMA, 3 RSI below 20, +D line below –D line).</li>
                </ul>

                <h3>Sell Rules</h3>
                <p>To enter a short (sell) trade, the following conditions must be met:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li>The 34 EMA must be below the 89 EMA.</li>
                    <li>The 3 RSI must cross under the 20 level.</li>
                    <li>The Stochastic must be below its Signal line.</li>
                    <li>The –D ADX line must be above the +D line.</li>
                    <li>The 3 EMA must cross under the 5 EMA.</li>
                    <li>When all these rules are satisfied, a sell order can be opened.</li>
                    <li>Set the Stop Loss above the 34 EMA or the last swing high point.</li>
                    <li>Set the Take Profit at double the amount of the Stop Loss, or close the trade when an opposite signal is given by the 3 and 5 EMAs, 3 RSI, or ADX indicators (opposite signal: 3 EMA above 5 EMA, 3 RSI above 20, –D line below +D line).</li>
                </ul>

                <p>This system ensures disciplined trading by strictly adhering to these entry and exit rules, reducing the risk of emotional trading and increasing the probability of profitable trades.</p>

